EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Land Use Call-Up be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle:
By Council Member Garodnick
Pursuant to Rule 11.20(c) of the Council and Section 197-d(b)(3) of the New York City Charter, the Council hereby resolves that the action of the City Planning Commission on Uniform Land Use Procedure Applications no. C 070125 ZSM, a special permit to allow Use Group 6 uses at 45 East 78th Street (Block 1393, Lot 25), shall be subject to Council review.

EventItemTitle: Report of the Committee on Finance

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Resolution be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the discount percentage for early payment of real estate taxes be set at 1.5% per annum for Fiscal Year 2008.

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Resolution be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the interest rate be 9% per annum for Fiscal Year 2008 for non-payment of taxes on properties with an assessed value of not more than $80,000, or not more than $80,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments.
EventItemMatterName: Recommendations of the interest rate to be charged for FY'08 for non-payment of taxes on real estate, and for non-payment of water and sewer rents.

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Resolution be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the interest rate be 18% per annum for Fiscal Year 2008 for non-payment of taxes on properties with an assessed value of over $80,000, or over $80,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments.
EventItemMatterName: Recommendations of the interest rate to be charged for FY'08 for non-payment of taxes on real estate, and for non-payment of water and sewer rents.

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Resolution be Approved, by Council approved by consent Roll Call.
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the interest rate to be charged for Fiscal Year 2008 for non-payment of water rents and sewer rents be 18% per annum for real property where the assessed value is over $80,000, or over $80,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments; and 9% per annum for real property where the assessed value is not more than $80,000, or not more $80,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments.
EventItemMatterName: Recommendations of the interest rate to be charged for FY'08 for non-payment of taxes on real estate, and for non-payment of water and sewer rents.

EventItemActionText: A motion was made that this Resolution be Approved, by Council approved by Voice Vote.

EventItemMatterName: Congress to end federal raids to deport undocumented immigrants and institute comprehensive immigration reform that protects the fundamental civil liberties of immigrants and integrates immigrants fully into American society.

EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the sale of toys and child care products that contain phthalates or bisphenol A.
EventItemMatterName: Sale of toys, childcare and child feeding products that contain phthalates.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Women's Issues
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling for the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, the Pay Equity legislative package.
EventItemMatterName: Pay Equity legislative package.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature to pass Assembly bill A.3763 and Senate bill S.3359, which would amend the criminal procedure law to enable judges, if so requested, to instruct juries in criminal proceedings to disregard appeals made to bias and prejudice through courtroom tactics such as “panic strategies.”
EventItemMatterName: Amend the criminal procedure law to enable judges, if so requested, to instruct juries in criminal proceedings to disregard appeals made to bias and prejudice through courtroom tactics such as “panic strategies.”

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the defacing or damaging of American flags on private property.
EventItemMatterName: Defacing or damaging of American flags on private property.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution declaring November to be New York City History Month.
EventItemMatterName: Declaring November to be New York City History Month.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature to amend the Hudson River Park Act to authorize a marine transfer station and environmental education center in the Gansevoort peninsula in lower Manhattan.
EventItemMatterName: State Legislature to amend the Hudson River Park Act to authorize a marine transfer station and environmental education center in the Gansevoort peninsula in lower Manhattan.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the discount percentage for early payment of real estate taxes be set at 1.5% per annum for Fiscal Year 2008.
EventItemMatterName: Recommendation of the discount rate to be allowed for prepayment of real estate taxes for FY'08.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the interest rate be 9% per annum for Fiscal Year 2008 for non-payment of taxes on properties with an assessed value of not more than $80,000, or not more than $80,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments.
EventItemMatterName: Recommendations of the interest rate to be charged for FY'08 for non-payment of taxes on real estate, and for non-payment of water and sewer rents.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the interest rate be 18% per annum for Fiscal Year 2008 for non-payment of taxes on properties with an assessed value of over $80,000, or over $80,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments.
EventItemMatterName: Recommendations of the interest rate to be charged for FY'08 for non-payment of taxes on real estate, and for non-payment of water and sewer rents.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution to establish that the interest rate to be charged for Fiscal Year 2008 for non-payment of water rents and sewer rents be 18% per annum for real property where the assessed value is over $80,000, or over $80,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments; and 9% per annum for real property where the assessed value is not more than $80,000, or not more $80,000 per residential unit for cooperative apartments.
EventItemMatterName: Recommendations of the interest rate to be charged for FY'08 for non-payment of taxes on real estate, and for non-payment of water and sewer rents.
